This file defines the core type definitions used throughout the DocMed repository.

### Key Exports:

*   **`ManifestEntry`**: Represents an entry in the documentation manifest, containing the file path, title, and a unique document key.
    ```typescript
    export type ManifestEntry = { filePath: string; title: string; docKey: string };
    ```
*   **`DocVersion`**: Represents a specific version of a document, including its timestamp, title, content, dependencies, and commit ID.
    ```typescript
    export type DocVersion = { timestamp: string; title: string; content: string; dependencies: string[]; commitId: string | null };
    ```
*   **`DocFile`**: Represents a single documentation file, containing its path, title, content, and optional version history and dependencies.
    ```typescript
    export type DocFile = { filePath: string; title: string; content: string; dependencies?: string[]; versions?: DocVersion[]; };
    ```
*   **`Commit`**: Represents a Git commit, including its ID, message, pusher, and timestamp.
    ```typescript
    export type Commit = { id: string; message: string; pusher: string; timestamp: string };
    ```
*   **`DependencyGraph`**: A record mapping document keys to an array of their dependencies.
    ```typescript
    export type DependencyGraph = Record<string, string[]>;
    ```
*   **`View`**: Discriminated union representing different possible views within the application (home, commits, specific document, folder).
    ```typescript
    export type View =
      | { type: "home" }
      | { type: "commits" }
      | { type: "doc"; key: string }
      | { type: "folder"; path: string };
    ```
*   **`Tab`**: Represents a tab in the UI, linking an ID, a `View`, and a user-facing label.
    ```typescript
    export type Tab = { id: string; view: View; label: string };
    ```

### Usage Example:

These types are crucial for ensuring type safety when handling documentation data, Git commits, and UI state within the DocMed application.
